// Project-wide build configuration.
//
// `Secrets.xcconfig` is the gitignored sibling that overrides these defaults
// with the real values per developer / per environment. `#include?` makes the
// include OPTIONAL — Xcode silently skips it when the file is missing, which
// lets a fresh clone build without copying anything by hand. CI populates
// Secrets.xcconfig from a repo secret before the build step runs.
//
// Add new shared settings here; add new secrets to Secrets.xcconfig.example
// (the committed template) so other devs know what to set.

// MARK: Defaults (overridden by Secrets.xcconfig when present)

OPEN_WEATHER_API_KEY =

// MARK: Optional override

#include? "Secrets.xcconfig"
